The People of the State of Illinois, defendant in error, v. Samuel J. Andalman, plaintiff in error.Gen. No. 34,204.Heard in the first division of this court for the first district at the April term, 1930.

Matchett, P. J., dissents.

Opinion filed December 1, 1930.

Rehearing denied December 15, 1930.

Cameron Latter and Ossian Cameron, for plaintiff in error. John A. Swanson, State’s Attorney, for defendant in error; Edw. E. Wilson and John Holman, Assistant State’s Attorneys, of counsel. Mr. Justice O’Connor

delivered the opinion of the court.
